The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for detecting cervical cancer cells/clumps in images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The method utilizes convolutional neural networks (CNN) and object detection techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of reference samples and limited data, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
